'''波羅蜥科'''（Bolosauridae）是一群已絕種的早期[[爬行動物|爬行動物]]，生存於[[二疊紀|二疊紀]]早到中期。化石在[[北美洲|北美洲]]、[[俄羅斯|俄羅斯]]、[[法國|法國]]、[[德國|德國]]、[[中國|中國]]發現；生存年代最早是[[石炭紀|石炭紀]]最晚期（[[格舍爾階|格舍爾階]]）或[[二疊紀|二疊紀]]最早期（[[阿舍爾階|阿舍爾階]]）<ref name=Parareptilia2>{{cite journal |author=Marcello Ruta, Juan C. Cisneros, Torsten Liebrect, Linda A. Tsuji and Johannes Muller |year=2011 |title=Amniotes through major biological crises: faunal turnover among Parareptiles and the end-Permian mass extinction |url=http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1475-4983.2011.01051.x/abstract |journal=Palaeontology |volume=54 |issue=5 |pages=1117–1137 |doi=10.1111/j.1475-4983.2011.01051.x |access-date=2012-06-26 |archive-date=2017-08-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170823232328/http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1475-4983.2011.01051.x/abstract |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |authors=Jocelyn Falconnet |year=2012 |title=First evidence of a bolosaurid parareptile in France (latest Carboniferous-earliest Permian of the Autun basin) and the spatiotemporal distribution of the Bolosauridae |journal=Bulletin de la Société Géologique de France |volume=183 |issue=6 |pages=495–508 |url=http://bsgf.geoscienceworld.org/content/183/6/495.abstract |doi=10.2113/gssgfbull.183.6.495 |access-date=2013-01-22 |archive-date=2016-06-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160601191340/http://bsgf.geoscienceworld.org/content/183/6/495.abstract |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

其包括的[[真雙足蜥屬|真雙足蜥屬]]是目前已知最古老的二足[[脊椎动物|脊椎动物]]<ref>Berman, DS, RR Reisz, D Scott, AC Henrici, SS Sumida & T Martens (2000), Early Permian bipedal reptile. ''Science'' 290: 969-972</ref><ref>Michael J. Benton ''Vertebrate Palaeontology'', pg.115</ref><ref>[http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/content/full/290/5493/917a?ck=nck Science mag article] (non free)</ref>。波羅蜥科的牙齒顯示牠們可能是[[植食性|植食性]]動物<ref>{{Cite journal|title=The cranial osteology of Belebey vegrandis (Parareptilia: Bolosauridae), from the Middle Permian of Russia, and its bearing on reptilian evolution|url=http://dx.doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.2007.00312.x|last=REISZ|first=ROBERT R.|last2=MÜLLER|first2=JOHANNES|date=2007-09|journal=Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society|issue=1|doi=10.1111/j.1096-3642.2007.00312.x|volume=151|pages=191–214|issn=1096-3642|last3=TSUJI|first3=LINDA|last4=SCOTT|first4=DIANE}}</ref>。

